    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1878-03-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1878-03-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="240" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d240">
                <head>No. 235.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Read</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Evarts</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1878-03-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 13, 1878</date>.
                            (Received April 13.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 370.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: To-day the King lunched on board the Vandalia
                        with General Grant, and spent two hours in conversation.</p>
                <p>The King came officially, in uniform. He has indeed seized every occasion to
                        manifest his respect for General Grant, and the feelings of His Majesty have
                        been fully shared by his subjects, who have displayed, great enthusiasm
                        whenever General Grant has appeared in the streets.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOHN MEREDITH READ.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
